`Final ThoughtsBoth approaches leverage dynamic programming to break down the problem into smaller, manageable subproblems. The recursive (top-down) method with memoization is often more intuitive to implement and understand conceptually. Meanwhile, the iterative (bottom-up) approach systematically fills a DP table and can sometimes be more efficient in languages like C++ due to predictable memory access patterns.

When working in Python, pay close attention to recursion limits and potential performance issues with large inputs. Begin with the recursive solution for clarity, and if needed, refactor the solution into its iterative form.

